Armenia: Adana Massacre: An estimated 15,000–30,000 are killed.
Australia:
The first powered aeroplane flight in Australia is made.
Alfred Deakin become Prime Minister.
Belgium:
Death of Leopold II, King of the Belgians
Accession of Albert I as King of the Belgians
Cuba: U.S. occupation ends. José Miguel Gómez of the Liberal Party becomes president.
Philippine: Present-day University of the Philippines Los Baños in Laguna is established, first autonomous UP campus. Cityhood of Baguio (Act No. 1963)
Sweden: Stockholm School of Economics (Handelshögskolan i Stockholm) founded General Strike of 1909
